              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A natural iridium sample of K2IrCl6 (iridium salt).",
                "The iridium salt was mixed with KCl in ratio of",
                "m(K2IrCl6)/m(KCl) = 0.6798(8) and pressed to a pellet",
                "with diameter of 7 mm. The KCl is a binding agent",
                "which helps maintaining pellet integrity. The pellet",
                "was combined with a nickel foil of the same diameter",
                "and sealed in an aluminum capsule. In addition, a",
                "double-sided 193Ir electrodeposit on a 2.5-microm thick",
                " titanium foil was irradiated together with the iridium",
                " salt capsule. The 193Ir electrodeposit had a diameter",
                "of 5 mm and was also combined with a nickel foil."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two Silicon Drift Detectors (SDDs) to measure",
                "the X-rays following the de-excitation of the",
                "isomeric state of 193Ir."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV",
                "CHSEP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " An irradiation with 6 MeV neutrons for",
                "10 h. The neutron energy was selected to be below the",
                "193Ir(n,2n)192Ir reaction threshold of 7.8 MeV. The",
                "193Ir electrodeposit was placed at 1.6 cm from the",
                "end of the deuterium gas cell and the pellet of",
                "iridium salt was attached behind it. After the",
                "irradiation, the samples were transported to Los",
                "Alamos National Laboratory (LANL) where the pellet of",
                "iridium salt was processed in the radiochemical",
                "facility of LANL's Chemistry Division to purify the",
                "iridium from osmium and platinum contaminants and",
                "prepare counting samples. Reaction cross section was",
                "determined by means of measuring X-rays following",
                "electron conversion of the isomeric state at 80.2 keV",
                " (T1/2=10.53 days) in 193Ir."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The X-ray intensity was corrected for the attenuation",
                "in the samples."
              ]
            }
          ],
